    <main class="main-panel">
      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Illustrations</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">Use illustrations to guide action, explain complex workflows, and reduce uncertainty across endpoint management experiences.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">

          <!-- Intro -->
          <div class="doc-section" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            <p>In Prism, illustrations are functional visual aids. They help clarify empty states, explain deployment workflows, support onboarding, reinforce AI guidance, and humanize error recovery.</p>
            <p>A strong illustration system improves comprehension without increasing cognitive load in dense enterprise environments.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Illustration types -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="illustration-types">
            <h2>Illustration types</h2>
            <p>Prism supports <strong>three in-product illustration types</strong>.</p>

            <div class="illus-type-grid">
              <!-- Spot illustrations -->
              <div class="illus-type-card" id="spot-illustrations">
                <div class="illus-type-preview">
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 292 244" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
