                </div>
                <div class="illus-type-body">
                  <div class="illus-type-name">Ambient patterns</div>
                  <div class="illus-type-desc">Light visual texture that adds brand atmosphere without introducing new meaning.</div>
                  <div class="illus-type-sub">Use for</div>
                  <ul class="illus-type-list">
                    <li>Empty dashboard zones</li>
                    <li>AI recommendation cards</li>
                    <li>Upgrade banners &middot; Promo modules</li>
                    <li>Workspace welcome screens</li>
                    <li>Module landing pages</li>
                  </ul>
                  <div class="illus-type-sub">Rules</div>
                  <ul class="illus-type-list">
                    <li>Must stay behind content</li>
                    <li>Never compete with text contrast</li>
                    <li>Use subtle neutral or semantic tones</li>
                    <li>No strong directional meaning</li>
                    <li>Use only for large supporting surfaces</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>


          <!-- Illustration principles -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="illustration-principles">
            <h2>Illustration principles</h2>

            <h3>1. Use illustration intentionally</h3>
            <p>Before adding an illustration, ask: <strong>Does this improve task clarity?</strong></p>

            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card">
                <div class="card-label">Good use cases</div>
                <p>Explain patch rollback</p>
                <p>Clarify empty inventory</p>
                <p>Encourage first action</p>
                <p>Reduce fear in failure states</p>
                <p>Celebrate successful deployment</p>
              </div>
              <div class="dont-card">
                <div class="card-label">Bad use cases</div>
                <p>Decorative filler in dense tables</p>
                <p>Background art in modals</p>
                <p>Repeated illustrations inside drawers</p>
                <p>Random AI sparkle graphics</p>
                <p>Decorative dashboard corners</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <h3>2. Support the copy, never replace it</h3>
            <p>Illustrations must reinforce text. The user must still understand the message with the image hidden.</p>

            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card">
                <div class="card-label">Good</div>
                <p>Device + shield illustration beside "All endpoints protected"</p>
                <p>Clear headline paired with spot illustration</p>
                <p>Written CTA beside visual</p>
              </div>
              <div class="dont-card">
                <div class="card-label">Bad</div>
                <p>Illustration only with no clear headline</p>
                <p>Using illustration as severity indicator</p>
                <p>No written CTA beside visual</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <h3>3. Match operational emotion</h3>
            <p>Endpoint products include emotionally sensitive moments: malware found, policy failed, remote wipe triggered, deployment success, AI recommendation confidence.</p>
            <p>Illustration tone should match the emotional weight.</p>

            <table class="tone-table">
              <thead>
                <tr><th>Tone</th><th>Context</th><th>Visual approach</th></tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><strong>Neutral</strong></td><td>Empty states</td><td>Calm, minimal, informational</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Calm confidence</strong></td><td>Onboarding</td><td>Welcoming, guiding, structured</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Encouraging</strong></td><td>Retry flows</td><td>Supportive, forward-looking</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Reassuring</strong></td><td>Recovery</td><td>Safe, settled, restored</td></tr>
                <tr><td><strong>Celebratory</strong></td><td>Large rollout success</td><td>Achievement, completion, pride</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>

            <p>Never use playful visuals for destructive or security-risk workflows.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Endpoint-specific patterns -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="endpoint-patterns">
            <h2>Endpoint-specific illustration patterns</h2>

            <div class="pattern-grid">
              <div class="pattern-card">
                <div class="pattern-title">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 12.75V12A2.25 2.25 0 014.5 9.75h15A2.25 2.25 0 0121.75 12v.75m-8.69-6.44l-2.12-2.12a1.5 1.5 0 00-1.061-.44H4.5A2.25 2.25 0 002.25 6v12a2.25 2.25 0 002.25 2.25h15A2.25 2.25 0 0021.75 18V9a2.25 2.25 0 00-2.25-2.25h-5.379a1.5 1.5 0 01-1.06-.44z"/></svg>
                  Empty states
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin:0 0 12px;">Best use case for spot illustrations. Each must pair: spot illustration + clear headline + single next-step CTA.</p>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="margin-bottom:0;">
                  <li>No devices enrolled</li>
                  <li>No failed patches</li>
                  <li>No active threats</li>
                  <li>No software inventory</li>
                  <li>No compliance violations</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="pattern-card">
                <div class="pattern-title">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.813 15.904L9 18.75l-.813-2.846a4.5 4.5 0 00-3.09-3.09L2.25 12l2.846-.813a4.5 4.5 0 003.09-3.09L9 5.25l.813 2.846a4.5 4.5 0 003.09 3.09L15.75 12l-2.846.813a4.5 4.5 0 00-3.09 3.09z"/></svg>
                  AI guidance
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin:0 0 12px;">Use low-fi workflow UI. Critical for trust in AI-assisted endpoint workflows.</p>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="margin-bottom:0;">
                  <li>"How AI isolates devices"</li>
                  <li>"How auto-remediation works"</li>
                  <li>"What this workflow will change"</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="pattern-card">
                <div class="pattern-title">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z"/></svg>
                  Security recovery
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin:0 0 12px;">Use calm, confidence-building spot illustrations. Avoid danger-red once issue is resolved.</p>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="margin-bottom:0;">
                  <li>Threat neutralized</li>
                  <li>Isolation completed</li>
                  <li>Rollback successful</li>
                  <li>Policy restored</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="pattern-card">
                <div class="pattern-title">
                  <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.59 14.37a6 6 0 01-5.84 7.38v-4.8m5.84-2.58a14.98 14.98 0 006.16-12.12A14.98 14.98 0 009.631 8.41m5.96 5.96a14.926 14.926 0 01-5.841 2.58m-.119-8.54a6 6 0 00-7.381 5.84h4.8m2.58-5.84a14.927 14.927 0 00-2.58 5.84m2.699 2.7c-.103.021-.207.041-.311.06a15.09 15.09 0 01-2.448-2.448 14.9 14.9 0 01.06-.312m-2.24 2.39a4.493 4.493 0 00-1.757 4.306 4.493 4.493 0 004.306-1.758M16.5 9a1.5 1.5 0 11-3 0 1.5 1.5 0 013 0z"/></svg>
                  Success moments
                </div>
                <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--prism-text-muted);margin:0 0 12px;">Use celebratory spot illustrations sparingly for major milestones.</p>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="margin-bottom:0;">
                  <li>100% patch rollout</li>
                  <li>All devices compliant</li>
                  <li>Zero critical threats</li>
                  <li>Migration completed</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Style system -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="style-system">
            <h2>Style system</h2>
            <p>Prism illustrations must visually align with Zoho Puvi typography, 1.5px icon strokes, rounded interface corners, semantic color tokens, and dark mode surfaces.</p>

            <h3>Style rules</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Rounded geometric shapes</li>
              <li>Clean enterprise-friendly metaphors</li>
              <li>Minimal scene depth</li>
              <li>Clear foreground focus</li>
              <li>Neutral supporting objects</li>
              <li>Optional semantic accent colors</li>
              <li>Dark-mode-safe surfaces</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Never mix illustration styles across modules.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Accessibility -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="accessibility">
            <h2>Accessibility</h2>
            <p>Illustrations must never carry critical meaning alone.</p>
            <h3>Rules</h3>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Always pair with text</li>
              <li>Decorative visuals must use <code style="font-size:13px; background:var(--prism-surface); padding:3px 8px; border-radius:6px; color:var(--prism-violet-light); border:1px solid var(--prism-border);">aria-hidden</code></li>
              <li>Informative visuals require alt text</li>
              <li>Preserve contrast in dark mode</li>
              <li>Avoid flashing success animations</li>
              <li>Do not embed text inside illustration art</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Illustrations support clarity, not accessibility bypass.</p>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Anti-patterns -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="anti-patterns">
            <h2>Anti-patterns</h2>
            <p>Avoid these common enterprise UX failures:</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li>Decorative threat illustrations in dense dashboards</li>
              <li>Screenshot-style UI inside onboarding</li>
              <li>Different illustration styles per module</li>
              <li>AI-only purple magic graphics</li>
              <li>Overly playful malware scenes</li>
              <li>Dense background patterns behind tables</li>
              <li>Large illustrations inside confirmation modals</li>
              <li>Using illustration instead of clear CTA text</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider">

          <!-- Principle -->
          <div class="doc-section" id="principle">
            <h2>Principle</h2>
            <div class="principle-card">
              <p>In Prism, illustrations reduce uncertainty.</p>
              <p>The right illustration system helps admins <strong>understand workflows faster</strong>, <strong>recover confidently</strong>, and <strong>trust complex endpoint actions</strong>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Feedback -->
          <div class="feedback-banner" style="display: none;">
            <div>
              <div class="fb-text">Help us improve this page</div>
              <div class="fb-sub">Share your feedback to help shape the Illustrations documentation.</div>
            </div>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px;">
              <button class="feedback-btn primary" onclick="window.open('https://cliq.zoho.in/company/60002085329/channels/prismdesignsystembyuemssupportfeedback','_blank')">Give Feedback</button>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <aside class="toc-sidebar">
          <h4 class="toc-heading">On this page</h4>
          <ul class="toc-nav" id="toc-nav"></ul>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>

  <script>
// Sidebar search: filter foundation nav links by query
    const sidebarSearchInput = document.querySelector('.sidebar-search input');
    const foundationNavItems = document.querySelectorAll('.foundation-nav li');
    if (sidebarSearchInput && foundationNavItems.length) {
      sidebarSearchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
        const q = e.target.value.trim().toLowerCase();
        foundationNavItems.forEach(li => {
          const text = li.textContent.trim().toLowerCase();
          li.style.display = !q || text.includes(q) ? '' : 'none';
        });
      });
      document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
        if ((e.metaKey || e.ctrlKey) && e.key === 'k') {
          e.preventDefault();
          sidebarSearchInput.focus();
        }
        if (e.key === 'Escape' && document.activeElement === sidebarSearchInput) {
          sidebarSearchInput.value = '';
          sidebarSearchInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));
          sidebarSearchInput.blur();
        }
      });
    }

    const themeToggle = document.getElementById('themeToggle');
    const moonIcon = document.getElementById('moonIcon');
    const sunIcon = document.getElementById('sunIcon');
    const currentTheme = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';
    if (currentTheme === 'dark') {
      document.documentElement.removeAttribute('data-theme');
      moonIcon.style.display = 'block'; sunIcon.style.display = 'none';
    }
    themeToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
      let theme = document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-theme');
      if (theme === 'light') {
        document.documentElement.removeAttribute('data-theme');
        localStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');
        moonIcon.style.display = 'block'; sunIcon.style.display = 'none';
      } else {
        document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', 'light');
        localStorage.setItem('theme', 'light');
        moonIcon.style.display = 'none'; sunIcon.style.display = 'block';
      }
    });

    // Dynamic TOC with scroll-spy
    (function() {
      const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.doc-section[id]');
      const tocNav = document.getElementById('toc-nav');
      sections.forEach(sec => {
        const h2 = sec.querySelector('h2');
        if (h2) {
          const li = document.createElement('li');
          const a = document.createElement('a');
          a.className = 'toc-link';
          a.href = '#' + sec.id;
          a.textContent = h2.textContent;
          li.appendChild(a);
          tocNav.appendChild(li);
        }
      });
      const obs = new IntersectionObserver(entries => {
        entries.forEach(entry => {
          if (entry.isIntersecting) {
            document.querySelectorAll('.toc-link').forEach(l => l.classList.remove('active'));
            const link = tocNav.querySelector('a[href="#' + entry.target.id + '"]');
            if (link) link.classList.add('active');
          }
        });
      }, { rootMargin: '-80px 0px -60% 0px', threshold: 0.1 });
      sections.forEach(sec => obs.observe(sec));
    })();
  </script>
<script>
(function(){
  const nav = document.querySelector('.nav');
  if (!nav) return;
  const toggle = () => {
    if (window.scrollY > 10) nav.classList.add('scrolled');
    else nav.classList.remove('scrolled');
  };
  toggle();
  window.addEventListener('scroll', toggle, { passive: true });
})();
</script>
<script>
(function(){
  const hamburger = document.querySelector('.nav-hamburger');
  const sidebar = document.querySelector('.sidebar');
  const backdrop = document.querySelector('.sidebar-backdrop');
  const navLinks = document.querySelector('.nav-links');
  if (!hamburger || !sidebar || !backdrop) return;

  // Build a mobile-only nav section at the top of the sidebar by cloning the nav links
  if (navLinks && !sidebar.querySelector('.sidebar-mobile-nav')) {
    const mobileNav = document.createElement('div');
    mobileNav.className = 'sidebar-mobile-nav';
    const heading = document.createElement('h4');
    heading.textContent = 'Navigate';
    mobileNav.appendChild(heading);
    const ul = document.createElement('ul');
    navLinks.querySelectorAll(':scope > a').forEach(a => {
      const li = document.createElement('li');
      const clone = a.cloneNode(true);
      li.appendChild(clone);
      ul.appendChild(li);
    });
    navLinks.querySelectorAll(':scope > .nav-dropdown > .nav-dropdown-menu > a').forEach(a => {
      const li = document.createElement('li');
      const clone = a.cloneNode(true);
      li.appendChild(clone);
      ul.appendChild(li);
    });
    mobileNav.appendChild(ul);
    sidebar.insertBefore(mobileNav, sidebar.firstChild);
  }

  const open = () => {
    sidebar.classList.add('open');
    backdrop.classList.add('open');
    document.body.classList.add('sidebar-locked');
    hamburger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
  };
  const close = () => {
    sidebar.classList.remove('open');
    backdrop.classList.remove('open');
    document.body.classList.remove('sidebar-locked');
    hamburger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
  };
  hamburger.addEventListener('click', () => sidebar.classList.contains('open') ? close() : open());
  backdrop.addEventListener('click', close);
  document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => { if (e.key === 'Escape' && sidebar.classList.contains('open')) close(); });
  sidebar.addEventListener('click', (e) => { if (e.target.closest('a')) close(); });
})();
</script>

